# Third-party reference checkouts (dspy, langgraph, haystack, claude-code,
# openclaw, ragas, openai-agents-python, lm-evaluation-harness, agent-framework)
# are a local-dev convention that lives outside this repo. PR #1 documented
# these as intentionally left as relative paths.
^.*reference-repos/.*$

# Stale paths into factory that PR #1 documented as "intentionally left alone":
# - `../scripts` — factory/scripts/ was removed in the repo split.
# - `../helm`, `../docker` — no such directories exist in factory/, likely
#   stale or planned. Excluded here so lychee doesn't surface them every run.
^file:///home/runner/work/docs/scripts/?$
^file:///home/runner/work/docs/docker/?$
^file:///home/runner/work/docs/helm/?$

# Local "architecture studies/*.md" pages referenced in MODULE-CATALOG.md but
# never imported when docs/ was carved out of factory. Real link rot, tracked
# separately — excluded here so the lychee gate isn't blocked by it.
^file:///home/runner/work/docs/docs/architecture%20studies/.*$

# npmjs.com returns 403 to CI link-checkers (bot blocking), so the valid
# @colbymchenry/codegraph package link in build-roadmap.md false-positives.
# The package page exists and resolves in a browser; exclude npm package URLs.
^https?://(www\.)?npmjs\.com/
